com.google.openbidder.api.bidding

Enum BidResponse.ResponseMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BidResponse.ResponseMode>
      • com.google.openbidder.api.bidding.BidResponse.ResponseMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<BidResponse.ResponseMode>
    Enclosing class:
    BidResponse

    public static enum BidResponse.ResponseMode
extends Enum<BidResponse.ResponseMode>
    The bid response builder will be in either "native mode" or "openrtb mode", mutually exclusive. The first time you use any of the response builder accessors, BidResponse.openRtb() or BidResponse.nativeResponse(), the response mode will be set accordingly. Mixed usage is illegal, so if you e.g. set the response to native mode and then try to obtain the OpenRTB-format response (directly, or indirectly via methods that depend on that), an IllegalStateException will be thrown.
